    {
      "type": "frame",
      "id": "eMrRh",
      "x": 524,
      "y": 716,
      "name": "Employer Breakdown",
      "context": "Employer Breakdown card - Shows list of employers with eligible days per employer. Displays: total eligible employers count, a green progress bar showing ratio of eligible vs total employers, then a list of employers with: employer name, days worked, eligible badge (yes/no). SCROLLABLE: When there are more than 4 employers, the employerRows container is scrollable (overflow-y: auto with fixed height of 154px). The card height does NOT change — content scrolls vertically instead. In React: scrollable div on the employerRows section. The 'Scroll for more' hint should only be visible when there are >4 employers.",
      "reusable": true,
      "width": 464,
      "fill": "$--card",
      "cornerRadius": 8,
      "stroke": {
        "align": "inside",
        "thickness": 1,
        "fill": "$--border"
